eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports. Courtesy #dstv403 DURBAN -  eThekwini residents are understandably not happy with the new rationing of water. The rationing kicked off Monday and will affect most areas in Durban. The restrictions are set to last 10 to 12 months while the eThekwini municipality repairs infrastructure damaged during the floods Residents are accusing the city of not having their best interests at heart. For full details, watch the video above.